The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, May 11, 2004 				 Archies in rejig mode
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, May 10: Archies Ltd is reorganising its operations with a growth target of 12 to 15 per cent over the next three years. The company is undertaking this exercise after going through a negative growth phase.																								Executive director Pramod Arora said, As part of the restructuring exercise, we closed the loss-making perfume division and decided to expand the retail business with focus on the core activity of greetings and gifts. Archies plans to set up 11 exclusive company-owned retail shops in malls across the country during the year. 
